<br>
If you have a person who by all outward appearances is anotomically male, and has been raised as one because of this, but for whom it's determined that they're a chimera and the brain actually belongs to the female twin...<br>
<br>
...if this person with a man's body and a woman's brain wants to marry another man, do you deny this person the right to marry or do you allow it?  Or do you only allow them to marry someone with opposite anatomy (despite them having a female brain) as is currently available to them.<br>
